Package: pcdp-lint
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Post-Coding Development Paradigm specification linter
 pcdp-lint is a command-line tool for validating Post-Coding Development
 Paradigm specification files. It validates structural requirements,
 META field formats, deployment template compatibility, and example
 block completeness.
 .
 Features:
  - Validates required sections and META fields
  - Checks SPDX license identifiers
  - Validates semantic versioning format
  - Supports strict mode (warnings as errors)
  - Lists available deployment templates